The Year of the Rabbit is approaching. Do you know the rabbit is actually a symbolic animal in many cultures? In addition to the rabbit that grinds herbs in the moon to the rabbit that relates to tequila shots, any other interesting rabbit folktales do you wish to learn about? Watch this episode to find more. About the 'Hopping into Tunian' series: Can rabbits drink water? Should you pull a rabbit's ears? What are the world's largest and smallest rabbit species? 2023 is the Year of the Rabbit, or Tunian, in the Chinese lunar calendar. For Spring Festival, we at CGTN Nature are presenting a new series, "Hopping into Tunian," to share funny stories about our buck-toothed buddies. (Video edited by Chenchen) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)